| **WCAG Criterion** | **Level** | **Current Status** | **Compliance Gap** | **Implementation
Priority** |
|-------------------|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------------------|
| **1.1.1 Non-text Content** | A | Partial | Alt text optimization needed | **Medium** |
| **1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum)** | AA | Basic | AAA enhancement opportunity | **Medium** |
| **2.1.1 Keyboard** | A | Functional | Focus indicators missing | **Critical** |
| **2.4.3 Focus Order** | A | Basic | Optimization needed | **High** |
| **2.4.7 Focus Visible** | AA | **Failed** | Complete implementation needed | **Critical** |
| **1.4.11 Non-text Contrast** | AA | Unknown | Testing and compliance needed | **High** |
| **2.3.3 Animation Interactions** | AAA | **Not Implemented** | Prefers-reduced-motion needed
| **High** |
| **4.1.2 Name, Role, Value** | A | Basic | ARIA enhancement needed | **High** |

## **BrainOps Strategic Implications**

### **Legal & Compliance Risk**
The current accessibility gaps, particularly the **complete absence of visible focus indicators**,
create significant **ADA compliance risk** and potential legal exposure. **WCAG 2.1 AA
compliance is the industry standard**[19] for legal protection.

### **Market Differentiation Opportunity**
**Only 14% of websites achieve comprehensive accessibility compliance**, presenting a
significant **competitive advantage opportunity** for MyRoofGenius to position itself as an
inclusive, professional platform in the roofing industry.

### **User Base Expansion**
Implementing comprehensive accessibility features could **expand the addressable market by
15%** (representing users with disabilities) while **improving usability for all users** through
better keyboard navigation and enhanced visual design.

### **Technical Debt Assessment**
The current accessibility gaps represent **significant technical debt** that becomes more
expensive to address over time. Implementing comprehensive accessibility now will **prevent
costly legal issues** and **establish scalable accessibility patterns** for future development.

**Methodology**: This audit combined direct website testing, automated accessibility scanning
principles, WCAG 2.1 compliance evaluation, industry best practice research, and comparison
with modern accessibility standards from authoritative sources including W3C, WebAIM, and
accessibility testing organizations.

**Limitations**: Assessment based on interface analysis and industry standards; comprehensive
screen reader testing, user testing with disabled users, and detailed automated scanning results
were not accessible for complete accessibility validation.

**Recommended Next Steps**: Prioritize visible focus indicator implementation and motion
accessibility controls while developing comprehensive accessibility testing procedures and team
training for ongoing WCAG 2.1 AA compliance and enhanced inclusive design practices.

